Well at like 11..Carmen came over and we went walking around..and talked. NO guys were out..that sucked. lol. We were walkin for about an hour..then she left. i coulda went to her house but my mom was bein a beyotch. So my mom n dad left and my coyusins were over my grandmas house..so i went there. kinda boring.. Later i sleptover theyre house. Fun.
    -- Sunday--
Wl i woke up and we watched t.v. we just did nuthin fer a while. then we walked to wendys for some food. When we got back, my aunt had to leave so i had to babysit for about 4 hours. For the first..eh...half hour it was boring. till my cousins 14 year old (hot) friend came over. i was all EEP! Ok well he came and at first we didnt talk. then he started asking me what school i go to and my grade and crap. And he kept sittin next to me on the couch..wherever i was..he was. So i was happy.Well him and my cousin were messin in therre room..then my cousin told me to find his friend. we were just tryin to find both of them for a while.Soon it became a game where the guys were blockin me and deanna (my girl cousin) from the couch. Of course Steve (my cousin anthonys friend) blocked me. He was all im blockin ashley! well he was veeeeeeeeery touchy feely...lik e major. Then he backed me into a corner, and turned around so our faces were practically touching and im like wo0t. Well i finally got out of the corner..and made it on the couch..so it was just me and him on the couch. Cuz my cousins anthony and deanna were still blockin each other..well since he let me sit on the couch (secretly cuz i wasnt suppost to) he had to hold my wrist, but instead he held my hand. i Was FREAKIN OUT! after we were all calmed down and anthony and deanna were out there too, he was still sittin next to me. We were really hot from runnin around so we went outsie. we sat at the picnic table..and he sat next to meee! eepity! so we all just hung out. Finally when i had to go...he asked me for a hug!! he gives great hugs..and not to mention..smells good. heh..grrrrrrrrreat day. AND i got money out of it. yay!
